  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large bowl, mix together blackberries, Greek yogurt, coconut oil, cinnamon, nutmeg, soy sauce, and honey until well combined.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x9 inch baking dish and smooth the top.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together eggs and shredded coconut until well combined.",
    "Pour the egg mixture over the blackberry mixture and sprinkle with crushed peanuts and salt.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 35-40 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the eggs are set.",
    "Remove from oven and sprinkle with fresh mint leaves for garnish.",
    "Serve warm, garnished with additional fresh mint leaves if desired."
  ],
